01:12.864 --> 01:13.782
Thank you.

01:13.865 --> 01:15.408
[audience whoos]

01:16.117 --> 01:17.118
Thank you.

01:19.621 --> 01:22.665
I was in the casino yesterday
with a friend of mine

01:22.749 --> 01:24.501
and he asked me
an interesting question.

01:24.584 --> 01:27.670
He goes, "How can you tell
which women out here are hookers?"

01:28.338 --> 01:29.881
And I thought about it and I'm like,

01:29.964 --> 01:32.717
"Well, normally if I smile
and she smiles back...

01:33.760 --> 01:35.762
[laughter]

01:37.388 --> 01:39.140
-[man whoos]
-that's the tell."

01:39.265 --> 01:40.600
[audience laughs]

01:41.017 --> 01:44.187
You don't need to send in the police,
big investigation, I'll handle this.

01:45.063 --> 01:45.897
"Hello."

01:45.980 --> 01:46.856
"Hi."

01:46.940 --> 01:47.982
"She's one."

01:48.066 --> 01:49.567
[laughing]

01:53.238 --> 01:55.115
I was watching a documentary

01:55.615 --> 01:58.284
recently about Flat Earthers

01:58.910 --> 02:00.411
that was fascinating.

02:00.495 --> 02:02.664
I don't know if anybody saw this,
there are people

02:02.747 --> 02:04.082
who believe the Earth is flat.

02:04.165 --> 02:06.668
-The documentary is called <i>Assholes.
-</i>[audience laughs]

02:07.877 --> 02:08.878
[applause]

02:11.131 --> 02:12.340
But I had to watch it.

02:12.423 --> 02:14.884
I'm like, I have to see if people
really believe this.

02:14.968 --> 02:18.012
And not only do they believe it,
they're adamant and they tell people,

02:18.096 --> 02:19.764
like, "You've been lied to
your whole life.

02:19.848 --> 02:21.516
They're lying about the shape
of the Earth."

02:21.599 --> 02:24.477
And all I keep thinking is,
"Why would anybody lie...

02:24.561 --> 02:25.478
[laughing]

02:25.770 --> 02:28.022
about the shape of the Earth? Who wins?"

02:28.106 --> 02:29.315
[continued laughter]

02:29.524 --> 02:31.442
When did this start?
Years ago, someone's like,

02:31.526 --> 02:33.611
"Look, I know it's flat,
you know it's flat,

02:33.695 --> 02:35.613
but if we can convince people..."

02:37.073 --> 02:39.075
[audience laughs]

02:43.746 --> 02:46.332
I'm dying to talk to a Flat Earther.

02:46.416 --> 02:49.043
There's so many questions.
Like, I'm trying to go with it.

02:49.127 --> 02:52.630
Maybe it is-- If it's flat, what happens
when you look underneath it?

02:52.714 --> 02:55.592
What do you see? Just a bunch of
Australians and Chinese people

02:55.675 --> 02:57.135
hanging by their feet like bats?

02:57.218 --> 02:59.220
[laughter and applause]

03:01.014 --> 03:02.932
I mean, if it was flat
the water would run off it

03:03.016 --> 03:05.768
and horses would fall off it
because animals are stupid.

03:05.852 --> 03:07.103
[laughing]

03:08.104 --> 03:10.899
But they have an answer for that.
The Flat Earthers have an answer.

03:10.982 --> 03:13.610
They say the reason the water stays on
and nothing falls off

03:13.693 --> 03:17.572
is because we are surrounded by
a snow-covered mountain range.

03:18.239 --> 03:19.490
And I was like, "Oh, all right.

03:19.574 --> 03:21.326
I was worried
you were going to sound stupid."

03:21.409 --> 03:23.328
[audience laughs]

03:24.204 --> 03:26.372
That makes perfect sense,
that we live on a serving tray

03:26.456 --> 03:28.833
-surrounded by mashed potatoes.
-[continued laughter]

03:33.546 --> 03:34.589
But they're not hateable.

03:34.672 --> 03:36.883
I enjoy-- I didn't dislike them at all,

03:36.966 --> 03:38.843
because a lot of conspiracy theorists
annoy me

03:38.927 --> 03:41.095
because you're denying
someone else's pain.

03:41.387 --> 03:43.348
9/11 conspiracy, Newtown conspiracy...

03:43.431 --> 03:45.808
They're denying that somebody else
has had a tragedy.

03:45.892 --> 03:47.560
These guys don't hurt anybody.

03:47.644 --> 03:49.812
No one is mad that they're talking about
the Earth...

03:49.896 --> 03:51.564
They're not like,
"Hey, the Earth is flat."

03:51.648 --> 03:53.858
-There's no one going, "Shut the fuck up!
-[laughter]

03:53.942 --> 03:56.986
I haven't sold a globe in six months.
Shut up!"

03:59.948 --> 04:03.159
Here's my problem with the whole theory
and conspiracies in general.

04:03.243 --> 04:04.118
If it's true,

04:04.535 --> 04:08.289
do you understand how many people
have to be in on the lie?

04:09.249 --> 04:12.168
Like, Flat Earth is by far
the biggest conspiracy

04:12.252 --> 04:13.378
ever conceived of.

04:13.461 --> 04:16.422
Because there's millions of people,
not just the government,

04:16.506 --> 04:17.340
not just the NSA,

04:17.423 --> 04:18.633
not just the FBI...

04:18.716 --> 04:20.969
People you wouldn't think of
that have to be involved.

04:21.052 --> 04:21.970
Boat captains.

04:22.053 --> 04:24.722
-Every boat captain who's ever lived
-[laughing]

04:24.806 --> 04:27.392
has to be sat down,
this has to be explained to...

04:28.101 --> 04:30.103
[continued laughter]

04:30.812 --> 04:33.147
I don't even mean just naval admirals.

04:33.231 --> 04:36.401
I mean every white trash
Carnival Cruise captain.

04:36.484 --> 04:38.486
[laughing and applause]

04:39.279 --> 04:40.697
They have to sit 'em down and go,

04:40.780 --> 04:43.491
"Look, you're going to be sailing
across the ocean.

04:44.367 --> 04:45.868
You're gonna see mountains.

04:45.994 --> 04:47.036
[laughter]

04:47.328 --> 04:50.456
Just... [mimics horn]
turn around, come back.

04:51.457 --> 04:53.459
-Don't say anything."
-[laughing]

04:55.920 --> 04:59.882
I saw a great documentary on Ted Bundy.
Did anybody see that?

04:59.966 --> 05:01.342
-That was a four-hour...
-[cheering]

05:01.426 --> 05:04.053
-four-part Ted Bundy documentary.
-[applause]

05:04.721 --> 05:08.516
And they said originally he wanted to be
an attorney or a politician,

05:08.891 --> 05:11.269
and when I heard that,
the whole thing kind of made sense.

05:11.352 --> 05:12.186
[laughter]

05:12.312 --> 05:14.605
Like, all right, he actually took
the more admirable route.

05:15.148 --> 05:17.108
[audience laughs]

05:19.027 --> 05:21.112
-[cheering]
-[man] Yeah, he did!

05:21.279 --> 05:22.238
[applause]

05:23.406 --> 05:24.449
[man 2] Yeah!

05:25.908 --> 05:30.288
And I've seen about 30 documentaries
on Ted Bundy and I got to be honest,

05:30.371 --> 05:33.416
I'm a little sick and tired
of the hero worship

05:33.499 --> 05:35.543
we have of serial killers in this country.

05:35.626 --> 05:37.670
I say "we"
'cause I've been guilty of it, too.

05:37.754 --> 05:41.466
But you can tell it's more than
just curiosity and voyeurism.

05:41.549 --> 05:42.383
It's admiration.

05:42.467 --> 05:45.094
You can tell by the language used
in the documentaries.

05:45.178 --> 05:48.264
They don't talk about Ted Bundy the way
they should talk about Ted Bundy.

05:48.348 --> 05:49.974
If they were speaking about him honestly,

05:50.058 --> 05:53.519
every sentence would start with,
"And then this piece of shit..."

05:53.644 --> 05:55.146
[audience laughs]

05:57.523 --> 05:58.441
But they don't do that.

05:58.524 --> 06:01.861
They give the obligatory,
"He was wicked, he was evil..."

06:01.944 --> 06:06.407
But then they find almost
admirable qualities and they harp on them.

06:06.491 --> 06:07.909
First of all, his intellect.

06:07.992 --> 06:10.328
They can't stop talking about
his intellect,

06:10.411 --> 06:12.705
which was overrated.
He was not that bright.

06:12.789 --> 06:16.125
They're like,
"Ted Bundy was so intelligent,

06:16.209 --> 06:17.794
he escaped from jail twice..."

06:17.877 --> 06:19.879
Do you know how he escaped from jail
the first time?

06:19.962 --> 06:22.590
The window was open and he jumped out.

06:22.673 --> 06:23.633
[laughter]

06:25.843 --> 06:27.261
That's how a cat or a bird

06:27.345 --> 06:28.888
-would escape from prison.
-[laughing]

06:30.723 --> 06:32.558
You're not a mastermind if you're in jail

06:32.642 --> 06:35.561
and you see an open window
and you're like, "Freedom is that way!"

06:35.728 --> 06:36.979
[continued laughter]

06:37.522 --> 06:38.940
They called him a genius.

06:39.023 --> 06:41.943
'Cause I think they like the idea
of the wicked genius.

06:42.026 --> 06:44.153
They actually said,
"Ted Bundy was a genius,

06:44.237 --> 06:45.738
he acted as his own attorney."

06:47.031 --> 06:48.491
They executed him.

06:48.658 --> 06:50.576
[laughter]

06:53.162 --> 06:54.330
He sucked as a lawyer.

06:54.414 --> 06:58.835
You're not a genius if you get the worst--
He couldn't have done worse. He got the...

06:58.960 --> 07:00.962
[continued laughter]

07:01.129 --> 07:04.006
