-[laughter]

13:40.486 --> 13:42.947
No one's ever like, "You look great,
have you been to the gym?"

13:43.030 --> 13:44.865
Like, "No, I tried to kill myself!"
"Fuck!

13:44.949 --> 13:46.033
[laughing]

13:46.325 --> 13:47.535
You really look good."

13:49.119 --> 13:50.412
There's been dark moments.

13:50.496 --> 13:51.413
There's been moments

13:51.497 --> 13:54.875
where if in my mind I knew it would
be fast, I would have done it.

13:54.959 --> 13:56.669
There's been a lot of times
where if I knew

13:56.752 --> 13:59.672
that I could just jump
in front of a train... Train! Dead!

13:59.755 --> 14:01.841
I would have taken that option, but...

14:02.258 --> 14:05.803
even in those sad moments,
I knew I don't have that kind of luck.

14:06.095 --> 14:08.097
-Um...
-[audience laughs]

14:08.514 --> 14:09.765
I'm not graceful.

14:09.849 --> 14:12.643
It would... Something would go wrong,
you know, it wouldn't be quick.

14:12.726 --> 14:13.811
Train! Dead!

14:13.894 --> 14:16.063
"Nope, it's dragging me.
It's dragging me."

14:16.146 --> 14:17.273
[uproarious laughter]

14:17.356 --> 14:18.732
[applause]

14:19.191 --> 14:22.152
My fucking face would be bouncing
over the railroad tracks.

14:22.236 --> 14:23.487
[continued laughter]

14:23.779 --> 14:25.030
They'd find me a mile down,

14:25.114 --> 14:26.574
crumpled under a subway car.

14:26.657 --> 14:28.284
"Relax, sir. We're going to get you out!"

14:28.367 --> 14:30.202
"Oh, that's great news, fellas.

14:30.286 --> 14:31.245
[laughing]

14:31.453 --> 14:33.914
I have no feet or shoulders."

14:40.254 --> 14:43.841
And I can see when I do this bit,
a couple of people are kind of like...

14:43.924 --> 14:45.384
[mimics uneasy groan]

14:45.551 --> 14:47.678
"Come on, Jim, shoot yourself.

14:47.761 --> 14:49.889
[audience laughs]

14:50.055 --> 14:51.849
Why make everybody late for work?"

14:51.932 --> 14:54.018
[continued laughter]

14:57.730 --> 14:59.189
Now, I would never shoot myself.

14:59.273 --> 15:01.191
First of all, I don't own a gun.

15:01.942 --> 15:03.527
Look, I believe in the Second Amendment.

15:03.611 --> 15:05.738
If you are mentally
and emotionally qualified,

15:05.821 --> 15:07.656
you should be able to have a firearm.

15:07.740 --> 15:11.493
I remove myself from that equation
because I know I can't handle it.

15:11.577 --> 15:15.205
I spike too high and I dip too low,
and I would misuse it.

15:15.289 --> 15:18.125
Even in good times.
You know, to celebrate, like I know...

15:18.208 --> 15:19.293
[laughter]

15:19.543 --> 15:20.669
it would be a problem.

15:21.670 --> 15:24.006
They wouldn't even sell me one.
I'd walk in, they'd be like,

15:24.089 --> 15:26.967
"What model would you like?"
"I don't know. Let me see how it fits."

15:27.092 --> 15:29.053
[oohs and laughter]

15:36.852 --> 15:38.938
But again, I would never shoot myself,

15:39.188 --> 15:43.317
simply because too many people
try to shoot themselves and live.

15:43.400 --> 15:45.402
-[yells of agreement]
-We've all seen those stories.

15:45.486 --> 15:47.196
Guy's wife is having an affair,

15:47.279 --> 15:49.865
he gets depressed
and puts a pistol under his chin,

15:49.949 --> 15:52.701
blows out the back of his mouth,
the back of his eyes,

15:52.785 --> 15:54.244
wakes up in the hospital in a month.

15:54.328 --> 15:56.872
-You can't eat, you're blind...
-[woman] Right!

15:57.039 --> 16:01.126
At that point,
you have to feel like such a silly goose.

16:01.210 --> 16:02.670
[audience laughs]

16:04.922 --> 16:07.299
'Cause you know she's not coming back now.

16:07.424 --> 16:09.426
[oohs and laughter]

16:11.136 --> 16:13.847
If she was fucking other people
when you had a face...

16:14.181 --> 16:16.183
[cheers and applause]

16:19.937 --> 16:24.149
Hose in the exhaust pipe
seems kind of quick and easy, doesn't it?

16:24.233 --> 16:26.652
You just kind of zone out and fade away.

16:26.735 --> 16:28.362
If I ever killed myself that way,

16:28.445 --> 16:31.949
I would wind up putting on a song
that I have no attachment to

16:32.032 --> 16:34.535
just to fuck my family up
for the rest of their lives.

16:34.618 --> 16:36.787
-[laughing]
-I'd write, like, "Listen to the words."

16:36.870 --> 16:39.581
It would be, like,
"Alejandro" by Lady Gaga and I just...

16:39.665 --> 16:41.625
-[audience laughs]
-[Jim chuckles]

16:42.501 --> 16:45.045
For the next 30 years,
[frantic] "What was he trying to tell us?

16:45.129 --> 16:46.505
-I don't know!"
-[laughter]

16:51.885 --> 16:55.514
Hanging yourself,
now that seems like a really, really...

16:55.723 --> 16:58.851
That's a dicey way to go
because, again, that's probably

16:58.934 --> 16:59.977
how I would do it,

17:00.060 --> 17:01.979
but there's different schools of thought
on that.

17:02.062 --> 17:04.898
Like, some guys hang themselves
and they kick the chair out.

17:05.024 --> 17:07.151
I am not that type of person.

17:07.234 --> 17:08.360
I'm not that committed.

17:08.485 --> 17:12.072
'Cause I know that I'd be swinging,
trying to grab the chair, like... "Ah!

17:12.156 --> 17:13.991
-[laughter]
-Come on, now. I was kidding!"

17:18.412 --> 17:19.663
I'm not committed enough.

17:20.122 --> 17:23.792
Aaron Hernandez of the Patriots,
when he hung himself in jail,

17:23.876 --> 17:25.961
he was doing life in prison,
he was never getting out.

17:26.045 --> 17:27.129
He really,

17:27.588 --> 17:29.757
really, I mean, made sure
that they couldn't rescue him.

17:29.840 --> 17:32.634
He put cardboard in the door
so they could not save him,

17:32.718 --> 17:36.847
he squirted shampoo on the floor
because this way if the guards came in

17:36.930 --> 17:40.017
they would not be able...  Or maybe just
to amuse himself as he's dying.

17:40.100 --> 17:42.311
It's like watching a Three Stooges sketch.

17:42.394 --> 17:44.396
-[imitates the Stooges, chuckles]
-[audience laughs]

17:46.315 --> 17:47.649
But he really planned it.

17:47.733 --> 17:48.650
I was in awe.

17:48.734 --> 17:51.904
I'm like, "That is the level of commitment
that made him

17:51.987 --> 17:54.364
-such a great football player."
-[audience laughs]

17:54.490 --> 17:56.575
[cheering and applause]

18:00.454 --> 18:03.457
And I did these jokes and a woman
came up to me after a show,

18:03.540 --> 18:06.126
and she goes, "Can I talk to you
about those suicide jokes?"

18:06.335 --> 18:07.753
And immediately I was annoyed

18:07.836 --> 18:10.798
because I figure she's going to try
to rescue me, which I don't need,

18:10.881 --> 18:13.092
or she's going to try to lecture me on how

18:13.175 --> 18:15.260
"Suicide isn't funny
and you shouldn't joke about it."

18:15.344 --> 18:17.304
I already know suicide's not funny.

18:17.387 --> 18:19.932
A subject doesn't have to be funny
on its own

18:20.015 --> 18:21.725
in order to be talked
about on a stage.

18:21.809 --> 18:24.603
-That's not how comedy works.
-[cheering and applause]

18:28.232 --> 18:30.776
You're all going to leave here
exactly as you walked in.

18:30.859 --> 18:33.904
None of you are gonna change who you are.
You're not going to walk out saying,

18:33.987 --> 18:35.781
"I didn't realize suicide
was so hilarious.

18:35.864 --> 18:38.325
-[laughter]
-I can't stop smiling thinking of

18:38.408 --> 18:40.786
-all the lives it shatters."
-[continued laughter]

18:42.079 --> 18:44.373
So she's like "I want to talk to you."
And I'm like, "What?"

18:44.456 --> 18:48.252
And she goes, "Have you heard about people
committing suicide in convertibles,

18:48.335 --> 18:51.004
where they're tying a rope around a tree,

18:51.088 --> 18:53.882
and the other end around their neck
and they floor it?"

18:54.216 --> 18:56.051
[audience laughs]

18:58.762 --> 19:00.472
[applause]

19:01.932 --> 19:02.808
Thank you.

19:03.392 --> 19:05.185
[uproarious laughter]

19:07.729 --> 19:09.606
And the last thing I will say,

19:09.690 --> 19:12.693
is we're a very divided country
and it's kind of

19:12.776 --> 19:14.403
startling how divided we are

19:14.486 --> 19:16.572
and I didn't realize how divided we are.

19:16.655 --> 19:19.158
I never realized how much
people didn't like each other

19:19.241 --> 19:22.953
until I was on a dating app
and I saw the political ideology

19:23.036 --> 19:24.955
taking precedent over everything else.

19:25.038 --> 19:27.416
Fifteen different women had things
on their on their profile,

19:27.499 --> 19:31.587
like, "Hey, if you voted for Trump
don't swipe on my profile."

19:32.546 --> 19:36.717
And I'm like, "Wow, do people care
that much about who you voted for?"

19:36.800 --> 19:38.468
-But, I guess they do, right?
-[woman] Yeah.

19:38.552 --> 19:40.095
Like, I didn't happen to vote for Trump,

19:40.179 --> 19:42.764
but if I had voted for him,
and I wanted to have sex with you,

19:42.848 --> 19:43.765
I would lie.

19:43.849 --> 19:45.809
[audience laughs]

19:46.435 --> 19:47.686
[applause]

19:48.145 --> 19:50.898
You're really overvaluing
politics in my life.

19:50.981 --> 19:53.567
Like, what do you think?
You're going to slide your panties off,

19:53.650 --> 19:55.235
and I'm gonna be like, "Whoa, whoa, whoa,

19:55.319 --> 19:57.821
back on till we talk about this trade deal
with China."

19:57.905 --> 19:59.781
[laughter]

20:00.532 --> 20:02.075
No, I'm going to lie to your face

20:02.159 --> 20:05.579
and then as I'm wiping your back off,
I'll yell, "Make America great again!"

20:05.662 --> 20:06.914
[cheering]

20:07.039 --> 20:09.208
Thank you guys very much. I appreciate it.

20:09.291 --> 20:10.584
[applause]

20:11.501 --> 20:12.794
